    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-15T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="598"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d598">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/6669: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Childs</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-10-15T22:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 15, 1942—10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>187. Your despatch 1015, August 31.<note n="54" xml:id="d598fn54">Not
                        printed.</note> The Board of Economic Warfare has lately taken the position
                    that no export licenses should be issued for supplies for Spanish North Africa
                    pending the conclusion of the proposed economic accord. Your view as expressed
                    in your despatch seems to favor the issuance of export licenses and navicerts on
                    a limited basis until the accord is concluded. The Board of Economic Warfare
                    desires to know what your present views are on the subject before considering a
                    possible relaxation of its present policy.</p>
                <p>What is the status at the moment of the negotiations with Orgaz?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
